{
  "stem": "802.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And we-- we-- I don't-- I think they put us into the trains, but I don't remember clearly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we got out, or else they never put us into the trains.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then we stayed there a couple of days and realized something was strange.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we walked out of that place where they put us into the-- or were about to put us into the camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And we were told the war was over.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "People, on camp.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and-- and the Germans, actually-- no, most of them fled.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Most of them fled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our own people told us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we did not believe it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother, my sister, I, and other people did not believe that, because we thought it was a ruse.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a lie-- that the Germans were waiting, poised with machine guns, to shoot at us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were afraid to leave.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Ultimately, we realized that, indeed, the war was over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, it wasn't over, because it was January 15, 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The war was still on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But, for us, we were sort of liberated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now I object very strongly to the word 'liberation' because we were never liberated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was no one to come to liberate us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They simply stumbled upon us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They found us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'm talking about the Americans, the British, the French-- whoever fought in the army-- certainly the Russians-- were not charged with liberating camps.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They just happened to have come upon them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they were horrified.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But it was in some way-- although the people who were in camps in Germany were in some way worse off, because the war lasted-- their liberation-- or 'release'-- let's call it 'release'-- from camps occurred later, in May, you know.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So they were there longer.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
